{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1c1ff9ab-661e-4bb1-b1a7-168c0caccb47","content":"If you still need per-test logging at setup time, move it to `[TestInitialize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[TestInitialize]\npublic void TestInit()\n{\n    var testName = TestContext.TestName; // works fine here\n}\n```\n\n### 3. Other v4 changes to watch for\n\n| Area | What changed |\n|---|---|\n| **`TestContext` injection** | v4 prefers **constructor injection** (`public MyTests(TestContext ctx)`) over the property setter pattern you're using. The property setter still works but is legacy. |\n| **`[ClassCleanup]` timing** | Now runs at end of class by default (v3 ran at assembly end). Add `[ClassCleanup(ClassCleanupBehavior.EndOfAssembly)]` to restore old behavior. |\n| **Inheritance** | `[ClassInitialize]`/`[ClassCleanup]` require explicit `InheritanceBehavior.BeforeEachDerivedClass` to run for subclasses. |\n| **Parallel execution** | Now on by default at the **method** level. Add `[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]` if tests aren't thread-safe. |\n| **Assert precision** | `Assert.AreEqual` for `float`/`double` is stricter about tolerance. |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8bf76173-3d27-4e06-91ee-0e93499bfa2c","outputTokens":324,"requestId":"CFC9:1FFE72:6679C43:72A7F8F:69EC2B89"},"id":"dd0a1add-9928-45ea-b716-ac09373b3c61","timestamp":"2026-04-25T02:48:49.823Z","parentId":"9f11a894-9a6b-4bef-8d16-1903dc3dec14"}
